In 2014, they began to prepare the Shippansee LTD application, which uses the already planned routes between the world's metropolises, mainly by plane, to transport packages.
In 2015, they commissioned a project to process the company that created applications for MALL.cz, Jobs.cz or <0xC4><0x8C>SFD.
The programming took three quarters of a year and the application was launched in March 2016.
The P<0xC5><0x99>evez app started development in December last year and was released this year in May.
This is a local version of Shippansee adapted for the Czech market.
The Mes<0xC3><0xAD>kem and Mes<0xC3><0xAD>kem Profi have been developed since January this year and made available to users at the end of July 2016.
The intention was from the beginning to make all these applications, which one day will merge into one.
In the Czech Republic, they want to tune the application and then, in cooperation with a strong investor, focus more on the global market.
The shared economy has been a topic lately, and this is an AirBnB or Uber service.
Don't you worry about working in an area that no one can say much about yet, where is the frontier of sharing and where is the grey economy?
It's the same, just a different product.
It is clear to us that if it succeeds and we go up with it, we will be another thorn in the eye through the grey economy.
But even though someone saves and someone earns, it is not the intention to circumvent financial authorities and tax controls.
Every user, whether on one side or the other, will be invited to give their income if they make it their income.
Why do you think the service has such great potential?
The sender saves and the carrier earns, respectively reduces the cost of travel.
That's the strong idea that connects interest on both sides.
In a time of social networks that divide people, we would like to bring them closer together.
Nice stories can come up, people are happy to help someone, and they will tell each other about it.
Maybe someone will bring you forgotten glasses, keys or pills.
In my opinion, people have been missing personal access for a long time, about this application we say that it is the service of people to people.
So how do you ensure that the courier with the package does not fly?
Each user of the app, along with the registration, scans the ID card and indicates a bank connection, payment or credit card.
These are the channels that give credibility to the service and the person.
The couriers also collect the stars based on the sender's rating.
We will also offer insurance, details are still being worked out.
The courier is responsible for the uninsured shipment in case of loss or damage, but does not accept responsibility for the content according to criminal law, if there is something illegal inside and he does not know about it.
If he is stopped by the police and found in a sealed package in his trunk, a slingshot or ten kilos of hashish, the criminal responsibility falls on the sender.
Is there a risk of misuse of sensitive data from the database?
They are registered if necessary by a searchable administrative authority, which as the only one will be able to look into it, even we are not able to see them ourselves, the data are protected against abuse.
How much money will the courier receive after successful delivery of the parcel?
The courier determines the price and gets the full amount he says.
The sender is charged a few percent extra for mediating the contact.
This money is our profit, but it's only a few percent because we want to push on volume.
Also, no one can accuse the courier of not delivering the shipment when it actually delivered it, the pick-up and delivery is verified using QR codes.
Are there any restrictions?
Whether in relation to the size or content of the package?
You can transfer anything.
We have three sizes, small as a butter cube, medium as a plate of eggs and large as a bass beer.
After that, there are no further restrictions and if someone has a place in the car, they will transport the refrigerator.
Plus, the sender has the option to take a picture of the package in the app, so the courier sees what is wanted for him.
You don’t even have to pack a thing unless you want to hide the content out loud.
You put the forgotten shirt in the courier's hand and that's it.
Who came up with the idea and how long did it take to launch the service?
A friend got the idea more than two years ago, I didn't pay much attention to it then.
Then he showed me a demo of an app with a transnational reach that targets mainly passengers by plane.
At that moment I told him that I would not be looking for an investor, but I would like to become one myself and put savings into it.
The next year was a year of development before we founded Shippansee LTD in London to increase the credibility of the entire product.
But this is not the version you are focusing on now.
No, marketing we focused on the Czech Republic, where we are trying to catch up with the application, because it all had birth pains and there is still something to solve and improve.
We try to respond to feedback from customers and the foreign market is currently not so much addressed.
We know it’s a long-distance run, but we’re not bragging, we want to create a really good product for people.
Shippansee LTD was the basic and most expensive application, the other two were in a way upgrades.
The transfer came about when we thought that the national segment could be much more interesting and that we would at least learn it in the Czech Republic.
The third application Mesikem is local, for the city.
But he can send the package to the exact address and to the other end of the world.
It works for the sender as well as the transfer, but the difference is that as a courier you see the shipments in the form of points on the map that are closest to you, thanks to the geolocator in your mobile.
The app for couriers who want to feed on it, we called Mes<0xC3><0xAD>k Profi.
So someone can make a lot of money by picking up packages in the city?
Precisely, the last application will be downloaded in Prague, for example, a taxi driver, a student, a mother on parental leave, someone who wants to earn a trip to work.
As much as everyone's messing with those Pokémon right now, they can collect this just the same.
One sees where the orders are in the city, comes to it, clicks and sees when it has to be delivered and transports the shipment.
It is set cheaper than competitive services.
At the moment, we are still making a web interface, which will be key for companies to send shipments, fill in data about them on the website, or create points on the map.
We are then able to bill them for the use of the service, for example, every month.
Are you currently working on a full-time project?
It takes advantage of us, but we normally have it on the job so that we can support and develop the project.
There is no strong multinational investor behind us, we are two guys, one of whom had a brilliant idea and the other jumped into it with other incentives and ideas.
Now we are looking for an investor strong enough to manage with us not the Czech market, but who should go with us in the global product and become another huge player in the market like AirBnB and Uber.
