Thirty years ago, at the time of my retirement, my wife, after thirty years of marriage, found a twenty-year-old man, our neighbor.
I knew it from the beginning - first she obviously tried it for a long time, then they put it together.
He's such a big guy, probably her type, because she used to date a guy like that in front of me.
She's gone mad at him.
In those first days, her voice even changed, she had such a girl, in love with a voice.
But when I told her I knew what was going on, she denied it.
But I watched the whole thing.
He then left work regularly at half past four, and so she always left at three to buy.
Every day she tried to see him, at least.
Later, I found out that they were meeting at his house, in the laundry room.
How many times did I know they were there?
I got the keys, he was determined to catch them there.
But I don't know why, after all, I always stayed at home.
I've never been able to go there, to take that decisive step.
You may laugh at me, but I believe that my wife controlled me mentally.
She soon found out that I was controllable, that I was going to do what she wanted.
And I really did.
Maybe I'm just a puppet.
My neighbors told me that they knew that too.
I was so stupid that I never asked them what to do.
I was afraid that if it all broke, it would be bad.
That it would affect everyone in the family, only the daughter knew something.
So I always put it off, on and on.
But one day I went to his apartment to get help with something in the laundry room.
He went there with me and I told him that I got anonymous, that he is meeting with my wife and that everything is pointing to it.
I asked him what he would say to me.
He stood there, shrugged his shoulders, looked down, and said nothing.
Then I also met his wife on the way out of the store at the time.
I told her, but she didn't believe it at all.
She didn't react to it, and she didn't tell me anything either.
No one told me anything at the time.
I'm the kind of person who's never been around much, who's having trouble getting to know someone, let alone finding a woman.
So I didn't even think about divorce.
I was always hoping that one day it would end.
I thought I'd forgive her for all this, and life would go on.
That's not how it was.
And I've basically never dealt with all of this.
I still have it in me today.
I used to tell her often enough, but in the end I let it go.
He's still living in the next house and I'm still living with her.
It's just that she's more like my wife than my housekeeper.
She always did everything at home - cooking, washing, cleaning.
She's busy.
She always tried not to give me any other reason to complain.
And you can say she's good.
But sometimes I want to stroke her, hug her, and she won't let go.
We go for walks and shopping together, and everyone thinks what a happy marriage we have.
But she once told me she never loved me.
That she loved me and loved me, but that she didn't love me.
And I see that she loves him to this day, he's her god.
And I'm not tired of that kind of life.
Even when it started and I carried it very badly, I once told her that I did not want to live and asked what she would say to it if I finished it.
I wanted to know if she would agree or not.
And that's what I wanted to hear from her: yes or no.
But she thought about it and finally said, "But there's plenty of room here."
