Hooker also played a key role in resisting the Islamic State’s intelligence services.
Last year, authorities announced that Hooker's team had concluded that despite public statements of the contrary, the airstrikes against Islamic State refineries had not significantly weakened the financial resources of this terrorist group, as the group had built a temporary refinery for the oil and gas industry.
The Times reported in September that the findings, however, were not passed on outside the central headquarters.
